videos.description: Nick Ward collects his own rebound and throws down a mean one-handed jam and a few possessions later, rises up for another one.
videos.headline: Ward throws down two emphatic slams

videos.description: Miles Bridges drives the baseline and delivers a huge dunk.
videos.headline: Bridges rises up for two-handed dunk

videos.description: Cassius Winston lobs up a beauty for Gavin Schilling to snag and throw down, forcing Purdue to take a timeout.
videos.headline: Winston tosses lob for Schilling's alley-oop

videos.description: Matt Haarms rolls off his defender and gets the pass underneath for the dunk and the foul.
videos.headline: Haarms beats the defense for slam dunk

videos.description: Cassius Winston holds for the final shot and is able to weave his way through for the layup to get Michigan State within 5 points at half.
videos.headline: Winston splits defenders to cut Spartans' deficit at the buzzer

videos.description: Isaac Haas continues his dominant day underneath with a turnaround jumper off the glass to boost Purdue's lead in the 2nd half.
videos.headline: Haas drains turnaround jumper to extend Purdue lead

videos.description: Miles Bridges works in the paint and goes up strong for the floater off the glass.
videos.headline: Bridges calls bank as Michigan State tries to open up lead

videos.description: After the timeout, Miles Bridges launches a deep 3-pointer to give Michigan State a lead with under 3 seconds left.
videos.headline: Bridges drains clutch 3 to put Michigan State ahead late

videos.description: An emotional Tom Izzo explains how Michigan State got the game-winning basket and why this game vs. Purdue meant a little more.
videos.headline: Izzo on final shot: 'We wanted to get it to Bridges'

videos.description: After hitting the game-winning shot, Miles Bridges points out that he wouldn't want to play for anybody else than Tom Izzo.
videos.headline: Bridges: 'We won this one for Coach'

videos.description: Bob Wischusen and Dick Vitale look at the all-around effort given by Michigan State and why this win solidifies them as a top-5 basketball team.
videos.headline: Bridges comes up clutch in Michigan State win

videos.description: No. 4 Michigan State overcomes a double-digit deficit in the first half and gets a go-ahead 3-pointer from Miles Bridges in the final seconds to beat No. 3 Purdue 68-65.
videos.headline: Michigan State tops Purdue late
